article.description: — Mark Freeman had a career-high 34 points to lift Illinois State to a 105-100 overtime win over Bucknell on Saturday night.
article.headline: Freeman carries Illinois St. past Bucknell 105-100 in OT
article.linkText: Freeman carries Illinois St. past Bucknell 105-100 in OT
article.story: NORMAL, Ill. -- — Mark Freeman had a career-high 34 points to lift Illinois State to a 105-100 overtime win over Bucknell on Saturday night. Freeman was outscored by the Bison's Andrew Funk, who had a career-high 38 points and added eight rebounds. Sy Chatman had 23 points and 11 rebounds for Illinois State (2-2). Josiah Strong added 12 points. Elvin Edmonds IV had 18 points for the Bison (1-3). Andre Screen added 11 points. Xander Rice, the Bison's second leading scorer coming into the contest at 14 points per game, scored four points on 1-of-14 shooting. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
